The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                The high court granted conditional bail to Pradeep More and Sushil Sureka, two directors of Stephen Court Limited, on Thursday. The directors will have to confirm their bail before a regular division bench by November 9 and submit their passports to police. The company is responsible for the upkeep of the Park Street landmark where a blaze on March 23 claimed 43 lives. Sanjay Bagaria, another director of the firm, was granted conditional bail earlier.    A cardiac patient, Gour Halder, 55, died on his way to NRS Hospital after the driver of the ambulance lost control and rammed into a truck on the EM Bypass near Science City early on Thursday. Halders nephew, Sanjay, 24, also died in the accident.    A youth died when a car hit the bike he was riding on Red Road, near Mohammedan Sporting Club, on Thursday. Sheikh Shamser, 32, and pillion rider Mohammed Tanvir, both residents of Phears Lane, were thrown off the bike. The duo were taken to SSKM Hospital, where Shamser was declared dead.    An army lance naik died after a truck hit him near the Hastings crossing on Thursday. Aibuddin Sheikh, 35, was cycling around 7.30am when the truck mowed him down from behind.    Power supply may be disrupted in the Mukundapur, Nayabad, Daspara, Green Park and Nitai Nagar areas on the southern fringes between 9am and 5pm on Saturday because of maintenance by CESC.    A private airlines push-back trolley hit a chartered plane stationed at parking bay No. 17 of Dum Dum airport early on Thursday. An airport official said the plane sustained minor damage.    Eight-year-old Kajal Majhi and her brother Sanket Majhi, 5  residents of Nimtala in Howrah  drowned in the Hooghly around 12.30pm on Thursday. Police said the kids were swept away by the tide at Nimtala-Panchanantala ghat where they had gone with neighbours for a bath.    A fire broke out in a ground-floor air-conditioner of the Suraksha block of NRS Hospital on Thursday evening. Two tenders doused the flames.    Swapan Mondal, 30, was arrested at Tehatta in Nadia by officers of Dum Dum police station on Thursday in connection with the murder of his stepmother Subhadra Mondal in a Dum Dum house about a fortnight ago.                                                                                                                                                  
